This question already has answers here : Closed 11 years ago . Possible Duplicate: Finding the adjoint of an operator Consider the vector space $C[0, 1]$ with inner product,
\begin{align*}
\langle f, g\rangle=\int_{0}^1f(t)g(t)\ dt.
\end{align*}
Let $T:C[0, 1]\rightarrow C[0, 1]$ the bounded linear operador given by, \begin{align*}
T(f)(t)=\int_{0}^tf(s)\ ds.
\end{align*}
How can I find the Hilbert adjoint operator $T^*$ of $T$?
